BIG NUZ member, Danger, found himself on the wrong side of the law recently. This is after he was arrested for possession of drugs. Sources said Danger, whose real name is Mzi Tshomela, was arrested at Amanzimtoti, KZN, on Sunday, 5 June, after police found cocaine on him. The sources said there’s a lot of speculation about his arrest. “It’s possible that someone tipped off the police that he had drugs on him. “We don’t know how the cops knew that they would find drugs on him. No one can be trusted in this world,” said one source. On the day of his arrest, he was meant to perform at Eyadini Lounge for the We Love Jigga Money show. According to the sources, he failed to pitch. ALSO READ : Naima Kay- is it LOVE? People who are close to him didn’t want to share more details about his arrest in order to protect his image. “Please call the police. They will tell you everything. Danger is my boy, so I can’t throw him under the bus like that,” said one artist, who is close to Danger. KZN police spokeswoman, Constable Thenjiswa Ngcobo, confirmed Danger’s arrest. Ngcobo said: “On 5 June at about 2pm, a 39-year-old male was arrested at Athlone Park in Amanzimtoti for possession of cocaine,” Our sources revealed that Danger will appear in court tomorrow. Daily Sun reached out to Danger for a comment but was unsuccessful.